This past weekend, two drug houses were found and searched in Pretoria east, and four suspects were arrested. Last Friday, the K9 Unit executed a search warrant at a house in the Faerie Glen area where there was suspected drug dealing. The house was then searched and the officers discovered that dagga was manufactured and sold in the house. Dagga plants and dagga in ziplock bags were found. The two adults, male and female, were arrested for manufacturing and dealing in dagga. The children were taken to a place of safety. During this arrest, more information about a second drug house in the Garsfontein area was obtained. Officers obtained a search warrant and headed to the house. Two suspects were found in the house. After searching the house, it was clear to the officers that drugs were being manufactured according to the evidence found. The two suspects were arrested for manufacturing and dealing in drugs. Staff Reporter Pretoria News